@edition "2026.6"

-- Theme system, Slice 4 ‚Äî the cycle proof (theme-design ¬ß3, styles-design ¬ß9.1).
-- A read-only theme root is acyclic BY CONSTRUCTION: a `theme.*` read adds no inbound
-- edge to the convergence graph, so a theme can never sit in a cycle on its own. The
-- only way back into a cycle is a CONTAINER QUERY ‚Äî an element that picks its surface
-- by measuring the very box that surface then sizes (measure‚Üítheme‚Üímeasure). Here the
-- box's `padding` is measured off its own resolved `width`, and its `width` is derived
-- back from that `padding` ‚Äî the ¬ß9.1 container loop. The (element, prop) cycle-checker
-- (¬ß6.2) rejects it with an edge pointer. Note `background=theme.panel` is a constant
-- read that adds NO edge: the cycle is purely the self-measuring width‚Üîpadding feedback,
-- proving theme's read-only-root status is what keeps the common case acyclic.

def view(): Element
  Row(gap=8)
    Box(padding=(self.width / 20), width=(self.padding * 20), background=theme.panel)

def main(): Unit
  println(html(view()))
